<task id="061" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Delete LegalWorkspace `SummarizeFiles/` fork (9 files)</title>
    <phase>Wave 4 — SummarizeFiles Migration</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>060</dependencies>
    <blocks>062</blocks>
    <tags>refactoring, cleanup, react</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Mechanical fork-deletion task; downstream impact handled by task 062 (re-exports). No ADR-bearing decisions beyond what 060 already locked in. STANDARD covers the cleanup + consumer-impact check.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Sequential: depends on 060 (shared canonical fix shipped) so deletion doesn't strand LegalWorkspace consumers. Blocks 062 (re-export shim) and 064 (LegalWorkspace deploy). Cannot parallelize within Wave 4.</parallel-reason>
    <fr-refs>FR-15, FR-25</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Delete the LegalWorkspace fork at `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/` (9 files per empirical pre-flight). All 9 files exist as a near-copy of `@spaarke/ui-components/.../SummarizeFilesWizard/` and one of them — `SummarizeSendEmailStep.tsx` — uses `sendCommunication()` (NOT inline fetch — but is still a fork to delete per FR-15/25).

    Before deletion: ensure no LegalWorkspace consumer breaks. Any import referencing `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/...` MUST be retargeted to `@spaarke/ui-components` (this is task 062's job — coordinate sequencing).

    Approach: this task DELETES the fork files only. Task 062 handles the consumer-side retargeting. To allow them to be done as a sequenced pair without breaking the LegalWorkspace build in between:
    1. THIS task: grep all consumers, document them in `current-task.md` for task 062
    2. THIS task: delete the 9 fork files
    3. Task 062 immediately follows: re-targets consumers OR adds a re-export shim
    4. Task 064 deploys

    The build WILL be temporarily broken between this task and task 062 — that is the expected handoff state. Do not deploy LegalWorkspace until task 064 (after 062).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend developer authoritative on LegalWorkspace component layout and the canonical re-export pattern. Familiar with the fork-vs-canonical distinction (per FR-25), the 9-file SummarizeFiles fork structure, and the LegalWorkspace consumer import patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/` directory deleted (all 9 files). Consumer audit list produced in `current-task.md` for task 062. LegalWorkspace build is expected to FAIL after this task (broken consumers) — that is the intentional handoff state, repaired by task 062.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per CLAUDE.md empirical findings: `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/` is a fork (9 files) of `@spaarke/ui-components/.../SummarizeFilesWizard/`. The fork's `SummarizeSendEmailStep.tsx` uses `sendCommunication()` (canonical typed wrapper, NOT inline fetch) — but it is still a fork per spec FR-15 (the directory exists as a duplicate) and FR-25 (LegalWorkspace must not fork shared-lib components).

      Forks exist because LegalWorkspace was developed before the shared lib had a SummarizeFiles equivalent. Now that the canonical lives in `@spaarke/ui-components`, the LegalWorkspace fork is dead weight + maintenance liability — every shared-lib fix has to be back-ported to the fork (which has happened inconsistently per the assessment).

      Deletion strategy: DELETE the fork files outright; rely on the canonical from `@spaarke/ui-components`. Consumer retargeting (task 062) is the immediate follow-on.

      Why not delete + retarget in one task: separation of concerns. THIS task is reversible (one `git revert` restores the 9 files). Task 062 is a separate atomic change (retarget imports). Keeping them split makes either reversible independently.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/ (PRIMARY — DELETE all 9 files)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/SummarizeSendEmailStep.tsx (fork uses sendCommunication(); not inline fetch but is a fork)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/ (audit for consumer imports referencing the fork)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/SummarizeFilesWizard/ (canonical — task 060 migrated to canonical pattern)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec FR-15">LegalWorkspace fork DELETED.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-25">No email-touching forks remain in LegalWorkspace post-Waves 3–6.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Re-exports MUST be from `@spaarke/ui-components` (canonical), not from local fork (which no longer exists).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Consumer audit list produced for task 062 — every file in `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/` that imports from the deleted directory.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Build break between this task and 062 is EXPECTED. Document in task notes. Do not deploy until 062 completes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Use `git rm -r` (not file-system delete) so the change is tracked and reversible via `git revert`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/plan.md</file>
